pageContext.claim: “I got in and say, how many federal judges do I have? Sir, you have 142 two federal judges. No, you don't understand the question. That's impossible. That would mean that President Obama didn't appoint 142 judges.”
pageContext.analysis: There were 103 vacancies on the federal courts when Trump took office -- not through Obama's lack of effort. Senate Republicans refused to move on his nominations.
